<p>I'm working within CMS Made Simple, part of which is a portfolio page which uses jQuery Shuffle to arrange and filter the options.</p>  <p>When you click on a portfolio item it takes you to a detail page, when you return to the portfolio I want the filtered items to still display.</p>  <p>I think the best way to do this is to use shuffles options and a Smarty variable passed from the URL. So I have this:</p>  <pre><code>Shuffle.options = {     group: '{/literal}{$vPortfolio}{literal}' }; </code></pre>  <p>If I just add this to my page it works but I lose the layout function, I've tried adding the Shuffle script it restores the layout but doesn't retain the filter.</p>  <pre><code>var DEMO = (function($) {     'use strict';      var init = function() {         var $grid = $('#grid'),             $sizer = $grid.find('.shuffle_sizer');          $grid.shuffle({             itemSelector: '.shuffle_item',             sizer: $sizer         });     };      Shuffle.options = {         group: '{/literal}{$vPortfolio}{literal}'     };      return {         init: init     }; }(jQuery));   $(document).ready(function() {     DEMO.init(); }); </code></pre>